body:
Thanks for pointing that out @snnn.

@oahzuw If you really want to build and train models, you'll have a much easier time _learning python_ and doing it there. The java API operates at a much lower level, enough to run an existing model, but you wouldn't want to work in it directly.

It looks like there's already a link to that `LabelImage.java` example on the [install/install_java](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/install_java) page. Does anyone have other suggestions on how to make it easier to find?
